We're gradually updating reward calculating to innovate miners scale up their generation volume
currently reward is calculated as: `final_reward = matching_reward * (0.8 + 0.2 * volume_scale)`
Where
- `matching_reward` is calculated if miner generate correct model, added latency penalty (max 0.4)
- `volume_scale` is calculated as: `sqrt(miner_total_volume / 1000)`
In future, it could be very competitive. The more gpus, the more incentive

### @nuance・23 - NicheImage Adding FaceToMany and Building a New Text Dataset for Model Training

Today at 1:00 PM we will push an update that will start supporting FaceToMany, and start using a Twitter dataset to bootstrap text generation prompts in order to create a new text dataset for training models on recent data.


### New Distribution
| GoJourney       | 4%  
| AnimeV3         | 33% 
| RealisticVision | 18% 
| RealitiesEdgeXL | 30%
| DreamShaper     | 6% 
| Gemma7b         | 3% 
| StickerMaker    | 3%
| FaceToMany      | 3% 

### Validators

If you are running auto-updates the update will be added automatically. Otherwise run:

```
git pull
pip install -e .
pm2 restart validator_nicheimage
```

### Miners
Miners don't need to update, and are recommended to stay at Bittensor 6.9.3 for now.

Registration will not be paused since the emission change is relatively small.


```
CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=1 /path/pm2 start /path/bin/python --name "REXL_miner_endpoint2" -- -m services.miner_endpoint.app --port 8002 --model_name RealitiesEdgeXL --num_replicas 1 --num_gpus 1
```
and then you can put a miner on a specific gpu

but really all you need to do is this:

```
/path/pm2 start /path/bin/python --name "REXL_miner_endpoint" -- -m services.miner_endpoint.app --port port --model_name RealitiesEdgeXL --num_replicas YourNumberOfGpus --num_gpus 1
```
and point each miner to it, it will distribute the tasks amongst your gpus for you
